MOP fonts
=========

Drop OFL-licensed font files in this directory.  The build system
bakes them into MOP's runtime atlas format (.mfa) and, for the HUD,
embeds the result directly into libmop.

Required for the embedded HUD font:

  JetBrainsMono-Regular.ttf

Fetch from upstream (OFL):

  https://github.com/JetBrains/JetBrainsMono/releases

The repository does not vendor the TTF — drop it here, then:

  make fonts          # bake → build/fonts/jbm_regular.mfa
                      # also emits build/fonts/jbm_regular.mfa.c
  make                # relink libmop with the embedded HUD font

After that, mop_font_hud() returns a usable font pointer with no
disk I/O.  Without the TTF, mop_font_hud() returns NULL and host
code is expected to fall back to mop_font_load() against an
on-disk .mfa.
